olive oil
1 packet Lamb rump
1 packet Green beans
1 packet Cherry Tomatoes
1 Lemon
1 packet Mint
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
1 packet spinach & rocket mix
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• See 'Top Roast Tips!' (below).
• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Lightly score lamb rump fat in a 1cm criss-cross pattern.
• Season lamb rump all over and place, fat-side down, in a large frying pan (no need for oil!).
• Place pan over medium heat and cook undisturbed until golden, 10-12 minutes.
• Increase the heat to high and sear lamb rump on all sides for 30 seconds. Transfer, fat-side up, to lined oven tray.

TIP: Starting the lamb in a cold pan helps the fat melt without burning.

• While the lamb is cooking, trim green beans and cut into thirds. Halve cherry tomatoes and lemon. Pick mint leaves.
• In a small bowl, combine Greek-style yoghurt and chargrilled capsicum relish. Season to taste with salt and pepper and set aside.

• Roast lamb for 15-20 minutes for medium or until cooked to your liking. Remove from oven and rest for 10 minutes.

TIP: The meat will keep cooking as it rests!

• Wipe out frying pan and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil
• Cook green beans, tossing, until tender, 4-5 minutes.
• Transfer to a bowl and allow to cool slightly.

• While the lamb is resting, to the bowl with the green beans, add tomatoes, spinach & rocket mix, mint (reserve a pinch for garnish), a good squeeze of lemon juice and a drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste.

• Slice lamb.
• Spread some chargrilled capsicum yoghurt on the bottom of each plate.
• Top with cherry tomato and green bean salad and roast lamb.
• Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, then garnish with reserved mint to serve. Enjoy!